sion\": {\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:562:              \"title\": \"Schema Version\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:616:              \"title\": \"Event Log Entry Id\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:628:            \"schema_version\": {\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:631:              \"title\": \"Schema Version\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:695:            \"composition\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:704:            \"completed_segments\": {\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:715:              \"title\": \"Completed Segments\"\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:717:            \"current_segment_index\": {\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:728:              \"title\": \"Current Segment Index\"\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:784:                  \"$ref\": \"#/$defs/CompositionInterruptionRequestView\"\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:850:            \"schema_version\": {\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:853:              \"title\": \"Schema Version\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:856:            \"segment_id\": {\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:866:              \"title\": \"Segment Id\"\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:868:            \"segment_status\": {\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:878:              \"title\": \"Segment Status\"\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:883:            \"total_segments\": {\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:894:              \"title\": \"Total Segments\"\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:957:              \"title\": \"Event Log Entry Id\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:969:            \"schema_version\": {\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:972:              \"title\": \"Schema Version\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:1019:            \"current_segment_index\": {\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:1030:              \"title\": \"Current Segment Index\"\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:1047:                  \"$ref\": \"#/$defs/CompositionInterruptionRequestView\"\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:1110:            \"schema_version\": {\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:1113:              \"title\": \"Schema Version\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:1131:            \"total_segments\": {\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:1142:              \"title\": \"Total Segments\"\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:1192:              \"title\": \"Event Log Entry Id\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:1204:            \"schema_version\": {\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:1207:              \"title\": \"Schema Version\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:1349:            \"schema_version\": {\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:1352:              \"title\": \"Schema Version\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:1419:              \"title\": \"Event Log Entry Id\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:1431:            \"schema_version\": {\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:1434:              \"title\": \"Schema Version\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:1495:            \"composition\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:1547:            \"schema_version\": {\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:1550:              \"title\": \"Schema Version\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:1606:              \"title\": \"Event Log Entry Id\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:1618:            \"schema_version\": {\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:1621:              \"title\": \"Schema Version\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:1679:          \"composition.chunk\": \"#/$defs/CompositionChunkRealtimeEvent\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:1699:          \"$ref\": \"#/$defs/CompositionChunkRealtimeEvent\"\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:1827:        \"schema_version\": {\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:1830:          \"title\": \"Schema Version\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:1889:        \"schema_version\": {\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:1892:          \"title\": \"Schema Version\",\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:21:        |         +--> AI adapters for planning, composition, and narration\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:23:        |         +--> repositories for sessions, workflow state, jobs, and event log\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:25:        +--> background workers for composition and audio generation\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:42:## Why Composition and Audio Must Use Resumable Server-Side Jobs\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:44:Composition and narration are long-running operations that cannot safely live inside request threads or browser memory. They need server-side jobs because:\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:47:- partial story text and audio segments need durable checkpoints\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:51:The durable model should include job records, segment records, asset metadata, and an event log that can reconstruct session progress after interruption.\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:63:- `ai/`: Gemini planning, composition, and narration adapters\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:73:- Event log\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:79:- Beat sheet\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:82:- Continuity bible\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:83:- Composition job and segments\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:84:- Audio job and segments\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:92:- `backend/`: FastAPI app with an app factory, versioned routers, settings loader, workflow models,\ndocs/system-diagram.md:10:    Worker[\"Worker process<br/>composition jobs, audio jobs, retries, interruption\"]\ndocs/system-diagram.md:12:    GCS[(\"File-backed GCS emulator<br/>story exports, audio segments,<br/>final artifacts\")]\ndocs/system-diagram.md:13:    Gemini[\"Gemini adapters<br/>planning, composition, narration\"]\ndocs/system-diagram.md:28:    Worker -->|\"planning, composition, TTS calls\"| Gemini\ndocs/README.md:14:- `event-taxonomy.md`: append-only event families, payload versioning rules, and helper usage\nbackend/tests/test_settings.py:51:        settings.gemini.approximate_pricing.composition.output_cost_per_million_tokens_usd\nbackend/tests/test_settings.py:77:            composition:\nbackend/tests/test_settings.py:112:        settings.gemini.approximate_pricing.composition.output_cost_per_million_tokens_usd\ndocs/contributing.md:30:- Version externally consumed HTTP APIs under `/api/v1` unless a compatibility endpoint is explicitly temporary.\ndocs/domain-model.md:10:- Backward edits are allowed on purpose and must mark downstream outputs stale instead of silently pretending they are still current.\ndocs/domain-model.md:11:- Composition and audio are long-running workflows backed by durable records, not one-shot request responses.\ndocs/domain-model.md:32:| `active_composition_job_id` | Current composition job, if writing or rewrite work is running. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:33:| `active_audio_job_id` | Current audio job, if narration work is running. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:41:such as pitches, character sheets, beat sheets, and setup revisions point back to the owning\ndocs/domain-model.md:56:| `beat_sheet` | Structured Save-the-Cat plan. | ordered beats, bedtime-adaptation notes, revision. | Must be editable and versioned. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:58:| `composition_job` | Parent job record for writing or rewriting text. | status, progress, attempt count, stop reason, current segment pointer. | Not listed in the prompt title, but needed to make `composition_segment` durable and resumable. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:59:| `composition_segment` | One planned or written segment of the story. | segment index, planned summary, text, revision number, superseded segment, status. | Supports interruption, partial persistence, and rewrites of earlier sections. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:60:| `audio_job` | Parent job record for narration generation. | voice, speed, music setting, progress, status, compiled asset pointer. | Audio should be resumable and segment-aware. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:61:| `session_asset` | Durable artifact metadata for session files and exports. | asset kind, object path, MIME type, byte size, checksum, segment index, readiness status. | Covers draft snapshots, composition segments, audio segments, `.docx`, and final audio without scanning object storage. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:62:| `event_log_entry` | Append-only session history. | actor, event type, stage context, payload with `schema_version`, created_at. | Supports replay, resume hydration, debugging, and audit. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:75:| 6 | `beats` | Beat sheet | One beat sheet is accepted. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:77:| 8 | `composition` | Composition | The current story text is complete enough to hand off to narration. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:90:The same four-state lifecycle should be used for stage rows and for generated artifacts that can become stale.\ndocs/domain-model.md:95:| `in_progress` | Durable work is actively being produced or updated. | Pitch generation is running, composition is streaming segments, or audio rendering is underway. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:96:| `completed` | The stage has an accepted output that is still valid relative to all upstream dependencies. | A beat sheet was accepted and no upstream planning change has made it stale. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:97:| `needs_regeneration` | The stage was completed before, but an upstream change made its accepted output stale. The old output may remain visible for comparison, but it is not the current source of truth. | The user edits characters after a beat sheet exists, so beats, composition, audio, and finalize become stale. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:112:`genre -> tone -> brief -> pitches -> characters -> beats -> story_setup -> composition -> audio -> finalize`\ndocs/domain-model.md:131:| `genre` | `tone`, `brief`, `pitches`, `characters`, `beats`, `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:132:| `tone` | `brief`, `pitches`, `characters`, `beats`, `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:133:| `brief` | `pitches`, `characters`, `beats`, `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:134:| `pitches` | `characters`, `beats`, `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:135:| `characters` | `beats`, `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:136:| `beats` | `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:137:| `story_setup` | `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:138:| `composition` | `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:145:- They still influence later composition, but a new pitch or character sheet does not automatically erase the user's preferred target length.\ndocs/domain-model.md:147:## Composition Interruption and Rewrite Rules\ndocs/domain-model.md:149:Composition is intentionally more flexible than the earlier planning stages.\ndocs/domain-model.md:151:- A composition job may move between `in_progress`, paused, resumed, or cancelled states without leaving the `composition` stage.\ndocs/domain-model.md:152:- Partial text is persisted segment by segment so a refresh or crash does not erase progress.\ndocs/domain-model.md:153:- A rewrite request against an earlier segment creates a new `composition_job` or new segment revision rather than mutating history in place.\ndocs/domain-model.md:154:- Superseded segments remain durable for comparison and audit.\ndocs/domain-model.md:155:- Any accepted composition rewrite marks `audio` and `finalize` as `needs_regeneration`.\ndocs/domain-model.md:156:- If the user decides the plan itself is wrong, they may navigate back to `beats` or `story_setup`, accept changes there, and let the backend mark `composition` and later stages stale.\ndocs/domain-model.md:166:   - Example: `composition`, `audio`, and `finalize` were `completed`, then the user edits the beat sheet.\ndocs/domain-model.md:167:   - Result: `composition`, `audio`, and `finalize` become `needs_regeneration`, and `resume_stage = composition`.\nfrontend/eslint.config.js:19:      ecmaVersion: 2023,\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:13:- Payloads are versioned with `schema_version`, even when a caller supplies raw mappings.\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:29:| `selection.recorded` | Accepted or candidate selection for genre, tone, pitch, character sheet, beat sheet, or story setup. | `user` | stage-specific |\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:31:| `content.user_edit.recorded` | Structured user-authored edits to durable planning or composition records. | `user` | stage-specific |\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:34:| `composition.progress.recorded` | Durable composition job progress for replay and worker debugging. | `system` | `composition` |\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:40:Those models all inherit from `EventPayload`, which guarantees a `schema_version` field.\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:46:  \"schema_version\": 1,\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:53:  \"schema_version\": 1,\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:57:  \"invalidated_stages\": [\"pitches\", \"characters\", \"beats\", \"composition\", \"audio\", \"finalize\"],\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:67:  \"schema_version\": 1,\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:75:  \"summary_text\": \"Updated beat sheet notes from the workspace.\"\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:80:`SessionEventLogService.append_event(...)` still injects `schema_version: 1`\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:96:- `record_composition_progress(...)`\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:104:actor defaults, and payload versioning stay consistent.\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:128:event_log.record_composition_progress(\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:130:    job_id=composition_job.id,\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:133:    current_segment_index=3,\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:134:    total_segments=5,\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:154:- Do not rewrite or delete historical events to \"fix\" history. Emit a new compensating event.\nbackend/tests/test_event_log_service.py:85:    event_log.record_composition_progress(\nbackend/tests/test_event_log_service.py:87:        job_id=\"composition-job-1\",\nbackend/tests/test_event_log_service.py:90:        current_segment_index=3,\nbackend/tests/test_event_log_service.py:91:        total_segments=5,\nbackend/tests/test_event_log_service.py:92:        segment_id=\"segment-3\",\nbackend/tests/test_event_log_service.py:99:        current_segment_index=1,\nbackend/tests/test_event_log_service.py:100:        total_segments=4,\nbackend/tests/test_event_log_service.py:101:        segment_id=\"audio-segment-1\",\nbackend/tests/test_event_log_service.py:139:    assert history.events[5].stage == WorkflowStage.COMPOSITION\nbackend/tests/test_event_log_service.py:147:        \"schema_version\": 1,\nfrontend/package.json:4:  \"version\": \"0.1.0\",\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:214:      label: 'Beat sheet',\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:216:        'Store the accepted Save-the-Cat beat sheet for the session.',\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:229:      stage: 'composition',\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:230:      label: 'Composition',\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:232:        'Write the story durably in segments, with room for interruption and targeted rewrites.',\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:379:  active_composition_job: null,\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:401:        schema_version: 1,\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:418:        schema_version: 1,\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:438:        schema_version: 1,\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:458:        schema_version: 1,\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:461:          'The current focus is softening the midpoint before composition starts.',\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:484:const sampleContinuityBible = {\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:485:  id: 'continuity-3',\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:488:  source_summary: 'Accepted beat sheet: Harbor lantern return.',\nfrontend/src/pages/