{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_322","type":"agent_message","text":"The duplicate insert is now fully explained: `run_job()` updates the job to queue the next segment but returns without persisting that state, so a subsequent run reopens segment 1 and collides on the same asset path. I’m checking the worker call path next; if it doesn’t commit externally, this is a real durability bug that needs a code fix, not just a QA workaround."}}
