{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_436","type":"agent_message","text":"Implemented and committed as `34a45bb` on the current branch.\n\nThe rewrite flow now supports range-targeted rewrites, preserves prior segment versions, exposes pending-review rewrite candidates, and marks downstream accepted segments stale when confirmation-mode rewrites are accepted. I also fixed a real durability bug surfaced during live QA: `run_job()` now commits queued-next, pending-review, and completed states before returning, so worker-owned composition progress survives fresh sessions.\n\nVerification completed:\n- Backend: `pytest backend/tests/test_story_tools.py backend/tests/test_session_hydration_service.py backend/tests/test_session_api.py` and `pytest backend/tests/test_migrations.py -k \"upgrade_from_zero_to_head_and_back\"`\n- Frontend: `npm --prefix frontend test -- CompositionStage.test.tsx`, `npm --prefix frontend run lint`, `npm --prefix frontend run build`\n- Lint: `ruff check backend/app backend/tests`\n- Browser QA against the compose stack, including pending-review and accepted stale-state screenshots under `.artifacts/webapp-qa/`\n\nThe required reviewer summary was written to [summary.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.yolopilot/runs/20260331T205548_storyteller_prompt_pack/66_rewrite_prior_segments_and_regenerate_downstream_text/summary.md)."}}
